@node intro " Quick Note v0.7 -- Introduction -- "

 Yet another release from myself to the public, this one however, is quite
incomplete in a way, though it is very functional, and at the same time looks
to be complete, but as I said, I still have a few tricks up my sleeves, these
tricks shall become alive in my future QN releases .

 So, why QN ? Well, I like the idea of having a wall, but alls are too
limited, users are limited to one line only, and if they do want to type more
stuff they have to go back to the wall ( in some cases disconnect & call
again ), and type whatever it is they wanted to . And users have to run all
around to the other side of the universe just to send a note to the SysOp, or
just a comment . That's why I combined all three elements and got them all
niceley in one door . I hope you do like this door ..

@endnode

@node Install " Quick Note v0.7 -- Installation -- "

 Oh well, now it has began to standardize, I managed to include an
installation script with this nice door, but as usual, you have to edit the
external command file I guess . So, just execute the script and all is all .
If you do want to install this door by yourself, then just dump all the files
in the archive into a directory in DOORS: called QN . That's it when it comes
to the installation . Make sure the Execute CMD is :

DOORS:rexx %N doors:qn/qn07.dd
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

 And then alter your Welcome.GFX file in Display/iso, add a new line with :
(the `Y' thing should preceed the sentance)

DOORS:qn/qnlog07.dd||

I think that should do the job just fine. Else, just drop me a line, I
wouldn't mind swearing at myself a few times :)

 That should be dead easy ... Else, please reffer to the mental hospital .


@endnode

@node how2play " Quick Note v0.7 -- How 2 Use it -- "

 You have the options, you deal with it, remember a comment is smaller than
the Note ;)


 Okay, okay, I'll teach you ! Erm... Nah, wouldn't bother ...

If you want to delete all the comments, sysop notes, and public notes, then
just load the files in a text editor and clear them and save them, don't
delete them, as the program sometimes crashes due to that ...

@endnode

@node bugs " Quick Note v0.7 -- Known Bugs -- "

 Well, the known bugs, there is a color bug in Quick Note Logon . I will deal
with it later .. Another is if a file is missing it would simply crash when
it doesn't find the file ... Typical . But shall be fixed too .

 The notes are not so "Arranged" as supposed to be, they could be damn messy,
and there is no support for cleared lines, ie, if you press enter in a note,
it will not save the space.... Again, pretty easy to deal with (I hope)


@endnode

@node future " Quick Note v0.7 -- Future QN Releases -- "

 Well, there shall be a few more QN releases, but soon to be followed by my
MEGA release PB, check it out in the other releases .

 Well, I shall assure you that all bugs will be fixed in the best way
possible, I will also optimize the code and make it as small as possible,
right now it' QN is barely 10K, but I'll try to get it to be 8K or so,
without serious altterations ... I know you might care that much, but I want
the door to load in as quick as possible, all the optimization in the code
might note be noticed when executed, but it will be initially faster .

@endnode

