@node other " Quick Note v0.7 -- Other Releases -- "

 Well, here are the other doors that I have made, or am working on right now,
and it'll be damn easy to find them here and ther on the AMINET, just check
comms/BBS .

SToryC, VoteX

Friend, Lunatic

Who's Who, SysOp's Up

WallX, Soccer ShootOut `98

 As for now, I have to MEGA projects, they are going to be damn big indeed,
well at least one will . The first is STooPid WorLD, which is an adventure
comedy, not the text based stuff, but more like text with a few graphics, and
I removed everything related to north/south/east/west, because a lot of
people hate that stuff, this project is going to be VERY big, that's why
there will be a lot of versions for it, I will have to optimize the code as
much as possible to keep it within normal human patience, it's going to be
nice though, that I assure you, I would love to find anyone that is willing
to help me on the ANSIs, also special BETA testing is demanded .. This game
is going to be my second game, preceeded by Soccer ShootOut `98 . I'm also
working on a bigger version of SS98, and hopefully will release it on to the
public soon .

 As for my second project, which is going to be a mixture of a few doors I've
created, it's going to be called Power Base (PB for short) It is going to be
a menuing system for Daydream, but with tons more options than the usual menu
available with Daydream, it will have new options like guest book, address
book, notes, special power walls, a few built in games, and also built in
bulletins, rather than using `B' in the normal menu, it will have a lot of
things, and already being implemented in it are Who's Who, SysOp's Up, VoteX,
Quick Note, and a few more doors .

 remember, I would be more than happy to give anyone early versions of these
two doors, I would also like to find some feed back, suggestions, and BETA
testers for these two doors . You know what to do .



@endnode

